          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Despite what reddit and twitter threads would suggest, not every game is improved by being ported to the Nintendo Switch. Unfortunately, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Lone McLonegan",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " seems to be yet another casualty in the Switch-port frenzy. While there is a lot to like about this quirky western point-and-click romp, my main takeaway was “Wow, I’d probably be enjoying this a lot more on a PC”. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
