      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Lone McLonegan",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " was a decent game that isn’t going to be as enjoyable on Switch as it is on PC. While it is an artistic marvel, the meat and potatoes of gameplay can’t keep up with the aesthetic garnish; the gameplay and structure are more annoying than fun for more than brief windows at a time. My time in Odella wasn’t entirely joyless but this definitely felt like a chore to get through. Bigger fans of point-and-click games and westerns than myself may find this game more satisfying but if you’re like me and hate using walkthroughs, this game doesn’t make enough sense at face value to be worthwhile. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Lone McLonegan",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is essentially a wonderful painting that you have to walk through a labyrinth to experience: some will find it more fun than others but either way, it’s a bit hollow.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
